### JWT Authentication Testing
### Test login endpoint with default admin credentials

# Variables
@baseUrl = https://localhost:7249
@adminUsername = admin
@adminPassword = admin123

### 1. Test Login - Valid Credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{adminUsername}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}",
  "rememberMe": false
}

### 2. Test Login - Invalid Credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "invalid_user",
  "password": "wrong_password",
  "rememberMe": false
}

### 3. Test Login - Empty Credentials
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "",
  "password": "",
  "rememberMe": false
}

### 4. Test Login - SQL Injection Attempt (Security Test)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "admin'; DROP TABLE TAIKHOAN; --",
  "password": "admin123",
  "rememberMe": false
}

### 5. Test Login - XSS Attempt (Security Test)
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "<script>alert('xss')</script>",
  "password": "admin123",
  "rememberMe": false
}

### 6. Test Login - Remember Me Option
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "username": "{{adminUsername}}",
  "password": "{{adminPassword}}",
  "rememberMe": true
}